Package commands

package commands
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    AbstractCommand
    The AbstractCommand class represents a template for implementing command objects in the command pattern.
    AddCommand
    The AddCommand class represents a command to add a new element to the collection.
    AddIfMaxCommand
    The AddIfMaxCommand class represents a command to add a new element to a collection if its value is greater than the value of the largest element of this collection.
    ClearCommand
    The ClearCommand class represents a command to clear the collection.
    CommandManager
     
    ExecuteScriptCommand
    The ExecuteScriptCommand class represents a command to read and execute the script from the specified file.
    ExitCommand
    The ExitCommand class represents a command to end the program without saving to a file.
    FilterStartsWFullNameCommand
    The FilterStartsWFullNameCommand class represents a command to display elements whose fullName field value begins with a given substring.
    HeadCommand
    The HeadCommand class represents a command to print the first element of the collection.
    HelpCommand
    The HelpCommand class represents a command that provides help information.
    InfoCommand
    The InfoCommand class represents a command to print information about the collection.
    Invoker
    The Invoker class is responsible for executing commands.
    MinByCreationDateCommand
    The MinByCreationDateCommand class represents a command to print any object from the collection whose creationDate field value is minimal.
    PrintUniqPostalAddCommand
    The PrintUniqPostalAddCommand class represents a command to print the unique values of the postalAddress field of all elements in the collection.
    Receiver
    Utility class for managing commands in the program.
    RemoveByIdCommand
    The RemoveByIdCommand class represents a command to remove an element from a collection by its id.
    RemoveLowerCommand
    The RemoveLowerCommand class represents a command to remove all elements smaller than a given one from a collection.
    RollBackCommand
    The RollBackCommand class represents a command to undo a change made.
    SaveCommand
    The SaveCommand class represents a command to save the collection to a file.
    ShowCommand
    The ShowCommand class represents a command to print all elements of the collection.
    UpdateCommand
    The UpdateCommand class represents a command to update a collection element by its ID.
